{"snp1.7":{"snp1.7:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 1.7 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 1.7 ","html":"<article id='snp1.7'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp1.7:0.2":{"pli":"Vasalasutta ","eng":"The Lowlife ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp1.7:1.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ me sutaṃ—","eng":"So I have heard. ","html":"<p><span class='evam'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:1.2":{"pli":"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ","eng":"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:1.3":{"pli":"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. ","eng":"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:1.4":{"pli":"Tena kho pana samayena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa nivesane aggi pajjalito hoti āhuti paggahitā. ","eng":"Now at that time in the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper’s home the sacred flame had been kindled and the oblation prepared. ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:1.5":{"pli":"Atha kho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami. ","eng":"Wandering indiscriminately for almsfood in Sāvatthī, the Buddha approached Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper’s house. ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp1.7:2.1":{"pli":"Addasā kho aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. ","eng":"Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper saw the Buddha coming off in the distance ","html":"<p>{}"},"snp1.7:2.2":{"pli":"Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ","eng":"and said to him, ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:2.3":{"pli":"“tatreva, muṇḍaka; ","eng":"“Stop right there, shaveling! ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:2.4":{"pli":"tatreva, samaṇaka; ","eng":"Right there, fake ascetic! ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:2.5":{"pli":"tatreva, vasalaka, tiṭṭhāhī”ti. ","eng":"Right there, lowlife!” ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp1.7:3.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā aggikabhāradvājaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca: ","eng":"When he said this, the Buddha said to him, ","html":"<p>{}"},"snp1.7:3.2":{"pli":"“jānāsi pana tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vasalaṃ vā vasalakaraṇe vā dhamme”ti? ","eng":"“But brahmin, do you know what is a lowlife or what are the qualities that make you a lowlife?” ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:3.3":{"pli":"“Na khvāhaṃ, bho gotama, jānāmi vasalaṃ vā vasalakaraṇe vā dhamme; ","eng":"“No I do not, worthy Gotama. ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:3.4":{"pli":"sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu, yathāhaṃ jāneyyaṃ vasalaṃ vā vasalakaraṇe vā dhamme”ti. ","eng":"Please, worthy Gotama, teach me this matter so I can understand what is a lowlife or what are the qualities that make you a lowlife.” ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:3.5":{"pli":"“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. ","eng":"“Well then, brahmin, listen and apply your mind well, I will speak.” ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:3.6":{"pli":"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi. ","eng":"“Yes, worthy sir,” Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper replied. ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:3.7":{"pli":"Bhagavā etadavoca: ","eng":"The Buddha said this: ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp1.7:4.1":{"pli":"“Kodhano upanāhī ca, ","eng":"“Irritable and acrimonious, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:4.2":{"pli":"pāpamakkhī ca yo naro; ","eng":"wicked and offensive, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:4.3":{"pli":"Vipannadiṭṭhi māyāvī, ","eng":"a man deficient in view, deceitful: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:4.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:5.1":{"pli":"Ekajaṃ vā dvijaṃ vāpi, ","eng":"He harms living creatures ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:5.2":{"pli":"yodha pāṇaṃ vihiṃsati; ","eng":"born of womb or of egg, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:5.3":{"pli":"Yassa pāṇe dayā natthi, ","eng":"and has no kindness for creatures: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:5.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:6.1":{"pli":"Yo hanti parirundhati, ","eng":"He destroys and devastates ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:6.2":{"pli":"gāmāni nigamāni ca; ","eng":"villages and towns, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:6.3":{"pli":"Niggāhako samaññāto, ","eng":"a notorious oppressor: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:6.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:7.1":{"pli":"Gāme vā yadi vā raññe, ","eng":"Whether in village or wilderness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:7.2":{"pli":"yaṃ paresaṃ mamāyitaṃ; ","eng":"he steals what belongs to others, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:7.3":{"pli":"Theyyā adinnamādeti, ","eng":"taking what has not been given: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:7.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:8.1":{"pli":"Yo have iṇamādāya, ","eng":"Having fallen into debt, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:8.2":{"pli":"cujjamāno palāyati; ","eng":"when pressed to pay up he flees, saying ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:8.3":{"pli":"Na hi te iṇamatthīti, ","eng":"‘I don’t owe you anything!’: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:8.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:9.1":{"pli":"Yo ve kiñcikkhakamyatā, ","eng":"Wanting some item or other, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:9.2":{"pli":"panthasmiṃ vajantaṃ janaṃ; ","eng":"he attacks a person in the street ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:9.3":{"pli":"Hantvā kiñcikkhamādeti, ","eng":"and takes it: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:9.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:10.1":{"pli":"Attahetu parahetu, ","eng":"For his own sake or the sake of another, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:10.2":{"pli":"dhanahetu ca yo naro; ","eng":"or for the sake of wealth, a man ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:10.3":{"pli":"Sakkhipuṭṭho musā brūti, ","eng":"tells a lie when asked to bear witness: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:10.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:11.1":{"pli":"Yo ñātīnaṃ sakhīnaṃ vā, ","eng":"He is spied among the partners ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Both Norman and Bodhi add a term suggesting transgression here, in line with the commentary and the apparent sense. I don’t, as I suspect the text is corrupt. Could <i lang='pi' translate='no'>diss</i> be <i lang='pi' translate='no'>duss</i>? "},"snp1.7:11.2":{"pli":"dāresu paṭidissati; ","eng":"of relatives and friends, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:11.3":{"pli":"Sāhasā sampiyena vā, ","eng":"by force or seduction: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:11.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:12.1":{"pli":"Yo mātaraṃ pitaraṃ vā, ","eng":"Though able, he does not look after ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:12.2":{"pli":"jiṇṇakaṃ gatayobbanaṃ; ","eng":"his mother and father ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:12.3":{"pli":"Pahu santo na bharati, ","eng":"when elderly, past their prime: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:12.4":{"pli":"taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:13.1":{"pli":"Yo mātaraṃ pitaraṃ vā, ","eng":"He hits or verbally abuses ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:13.2":{"pli":"Bhātaraṃ bhaginiṃ sasuṃ; ","eng":"his mother or father, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:13.3":{"pli":"Hanti roseti vācāya, ","eng":"brother, sister, or mother-in-law: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:13.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:14.1":{"pli":"Yo atthaṃ pucchito santo, ","eng":"When asked about the good, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:14.2":{"pli":"Anatthamanusāsati; ","eng":"he teaches what is bad, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:14.3":{"pli":"Paṭicchannena manteti, ","eng":"giving secretive advice: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:14.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:15.1":{"pli":"Yo katvā pāpakaṃ kammaṃ, ","eng":"Having done a bad deed, he wishes, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:15.2":{"pli":"Mā maṃ jaññāti icchati; ","eng":"‘May no-one find me out!’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:15.3":{"pli":"Yo paṭicchannakammanto, ","eng":"His deeds are underhand: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:15.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:16.1":{"pli":"Yo ve parakulaṃ gantvā, ","eng":"When visiting another family ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:16.2":{"pli":"Bhutvāna sucibhojanaṃ; ","eng":"he eats their delicious food, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:16.3":{"pli":"Āgataṃ nappaṭipūjeti, ","eng":"but does not return the honor: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:16.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:17.1":{"pli":"Yo brāhmaṇaṃ samaṇaṃ vā, ","eng":"He deceives with lies ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:17.2":{"pli":"Aññaṃ vāpi vanibbakaṃ; ","eng":"ascetics and brahmins ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:17.3":{"pli":"Musāvādena vañceti, ","eng":"and other supplicants: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:17.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:18.1":{"pli":"Yo brāhmaṇaṃ samaṇaṃ vā, ","eng":"When time comes to offer a meal ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:18.2":{"pli":"Bhattakāle upaṭṭhite; ","eng":"to brahmins or ascetics, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:18.3":{"pli":"Roseti vācā na ca deti, ","eng":"he abuses them and does not give: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:18.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:19.1":{"pli":"Asataṃ yodha pabrūti, ","eng":"He talks about what never happened, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:19.2":{"pli":"Mohena paliguṇṭhito; ","eng":"being wrapped up in delusion, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:19.3":{"pli":"Kiñcikkhaṃ nijigīsāno, ","eng":"chasing after some item or other: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:19.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:20.1":{"pli":"Yo cattānaṃ samukkaṃse, ","eng":"He extols himself ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:20.2":{"pli":"Pare ca mavajānāti; ","eng":"and disparages others, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:20.3":{"pli":"Nihīno sena mānena, ","eng":"brought down by his pride: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:20.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:21.1":{"pli":"Rosako kadariyo ca, ","eng":"He’s a bully and a miser, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:21.2":{"pli":"Pāpiccho maccharī saṭho; ","eng":"of corrupt wishes, stingy, and devious, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:21.3":{"pli":"Ahiriko anottappī, ","eng":"shameless, imprudent: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:21.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:22.1":{"pli":"Yo buddhaṃ paribhāsati, ","eng":"He insults the Buddha ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:22.2":{"pli":"Atha vā tassa sāvakaṃ; ","eng":"or his disciple, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:22.3":{"pli":"Paribbājaṃ gahaṭṭhaṃ vā, ","eng":"whether lay or renunciate: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:22.4":{"pli":"Taṃ jaññā vasalo iti. ","eng":"know him as a lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:23.1":{"pli":"Yo ve anarahaṃ santo, ","eng":"He claims to be a perfected one, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:23.2":{"pli":"Arahaṃ paṭijānāti; ","eng":"when he really is no such thing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:23.3":{"pli":"Coro sabrahmake loke, ","eng":"In the world with its divinities, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:23.4":{"pli":"Eso kho vasalādhamo; ","eng":"that crook is truly the lowest lowlife. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:23.5":{"pli":"Ete kho vasalā vuttā, ","eng":"These who are called lowlifes ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:23.6":{"pli":"Mayā yete pakāsitā. ","eng":"I have explained to you. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:24.1":{"pli":"Na jaccā vasalo hoti, ","eng":"You’re not a lowlife by birth, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:24.2":{"pli":"Na jaccā hoti brāhmaṇo; ","eng":"nor by birth are you a brahmin. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:24.3":{"pli":"Kammunā vasalo hoti, ","eng":"You’re a lowlife by your deeds, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:24.4":{"pli":"Kammunā hoti brāhmaṇo. ","eng":"by deeds you’re a brahmin. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:25.1":{"pli":"Tadamināpi jānātha, ","eng":"And also you should know ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:25.2":{"pli":"Yathāmedaṃ nidassanaṃ; ","eng":"according to this example. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:25.3":{"pli":"Caṇḍālaputto sopāko, ","eng":"A corpse-worker’s son of the dog-eating caste ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:25.4":{"pli":"Mātaṅgo iti vissuto. ","eng":"became renowned as Mātaṅga. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:26.1":{"pli":"So yasaṃ paramaṃ patto, ","eng":"Mātaṅga achieved the highest fame ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:26.2":{"pli":"Mātaṅgo yaṃ sudullabhaṃ; ","eng":"so very hard to find. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:26.3":{"pli":"Āgacchuṃ tassupaṭṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"Lots of aristocrats and brahmins ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:26.4":{"pli":"Khattiyā brāhmaṇā bahū. ","eng":"came to serve him. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:27.1":{"pli":"Devayānaṃ abhiruyha, ","eng":"He ascended the stainless highway ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:27.2":{"pli":"Virajaṃ so mahāpathaṃ; ","eng":"that leads to the heavens; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:27.3":{"pli":"Kāmarāgaṃ virājetvā, ","eng":"having discarded sensual desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:27.4":{"pli":"Brahmalokūpago ahu; ","eng":"he was reborn in a realm of divinity. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:27.5":{"pli":"Na naṃ jāti nivāresi, ","eng":"His birth did not prevent him ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:27.6":{"pli":"Brahmalokūpapattiyā. ","eng":"from rebirth in the realm of divinity. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:28.1":{"pli":"Ajjhāyakakule jātā, ","eng":"Those born in a brahmin family ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:28.2":{"pli":"Brāhmaṇā mantabandhavā; ","eng":"who recite as kinsmen of the hymns, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:28.3":{"pli":"Te ca pāpesu kammesu, ","eng":"are often discovered ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:28.4":{"pli":"Abhiṇhamupadissare. ","eng":"in the midst of wicked deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:29.1":{"pli":"Diṭṭheva dhamme gārayhā, ","eng":"Blameworthy in this very life, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:29.2":{"pli":"Samparāye ca duggati; ","eng":"and in the next, a bad destination. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:29.3":{"pli":"Na ne jāti nivāreti, ","eng":"Their birth does not prevent them ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:29.4":{"pli":"Duggatyā garahāya vā. ","eng":"from blame or bad destiny. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.7:30.1":{"pli":"Na jaccā vasalo hoti, ","eng":"You’re not a lowlife by birth, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:30.2":{"pli":"Na jaccā hoti brāhmaṇo; ","eng":"nor by birth are you a brahmin. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:30.3":{"pli":"Kammunā vasalo hoti, ","eng":"You’re a lowlife by your deeds, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.7:30.4":{"pli":"Kammunā hoti brāhmaṇo”ti. ","eng":"by deeds you’re a brahmin.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp1.7:31.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ vutte, aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ","eng":"When he had spoken, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper said to the Buddha, ","html":"<p>{}"},"snp1.7:31.2":{"pli":"“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama …pe… ","eng":"“Excellent, worthy Gotama! Excellent! … ","html":"{}"},"snp1.7:31.3":{"pli":"upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. ","eng":"From this day forth, may the worthy Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp1.7:31.4":{"pli":"Vasalasuttaṃ sattamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp1.8":{"snp1.8:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 1.8 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 1.8 ","html":"<article id='snp1.8'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp1.8:0.2":{"pli":"Mettasutta ","eng":"The Discourse on Love ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp1.8:1.1":{"pli":"“Karaṇīyamatthakusalena, ","eng":"Those who are skilled in the meaning of scripture ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"See <a href='index.html?q=an5.169#3.1'>AN 5.169:3.1</a> for this sense of <i lang='pi' translate='no'>atthakusala</i>. | <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Kusala</i> in the sense of “one who is skilled”, an “expert” is found occasionally in the canon, especially in the Aṭṭhakavagga. It appears also in early Sanskrit, for example, for those who are “skilled” in recitation (Chāndogya Upaniṣad 1.8.1), or for those who only think that they are skilled (Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 11.4.2.1, 4, and 13). "},"snp1.8:1.2":{"pli":"Yanta santaṃ padaṃ abhisamecca; ","eng":"should practice as follows <j>to realize the state of peace. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Reading the absolutive in an infinitive sense, an alternative given in the commentary: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>abhisamecca viharitukāmena</i>. "},"snp1.8:1.3":{"pli":"Sakko ujū ca suhujū ca, ","eng":"Let them be capable and upright, very upright, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:1.4":{"pli":"Sūvaco cassa mudu anatimānī. ","eng":"easy to speak to, gentle and humble; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:2.1":{"pli":"Santussako ca subharo ca, ","eng":"content and unburdensome, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:2.2":{"pli":"Appakicco ca sallahukavutti; ","eng":"unbusied, living lightly, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:2.3":{"pli":"Santindriyo ca nipako ca, ","eng":"alert, with senses calmed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:2.4":{"pli":"Appagabbho kulesvananugiddho. ","eng":"courteous, not fawning on families. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:3.1":{"pli":"Na ca khuddamācare kiñci, ","eng":"Let them not do the slightest thing ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:3.2":{"pli":"Yena viññū pare upavadeyyuṃ; ","eng":"that others who are wise would blame. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Compare <a href='index.html?q=an4.121#3.3'>AN 4.121:3.3</a>. "},"snp1.8:3.3":{"pli":"Sukhino va khemino hontu, ","eng":"May they be happy and safe! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:3.4":{"pli":"Sabbasattā bhavantu sukhitattā. ","eng":"May all beings be happy! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:4.1":{"pli":"Ye keci pāṇabhūtatthi, ","eng":"Whatever living creatures there are ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:4.2":{"pli":"Tasā vā thāvarā vanavasesā; ","eng":"with not a one left out—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:4.3":{"pli":"Dīghā vā ye va mahantā, ","eng":"frail or firm, long or large, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Creatures “firm and frail” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>tasathāvare</i>) is a common Jain idiom (eg. Uttarādhyayana 5.8: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tasesu thāvaresu ya</i>; Sūyagaḍa 3.4.20: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>je keī tasathāvarā</i>; Dasaveyāliya 4.1.42: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tasaṁ vā thāvaraṁ vā</i>; Ācāraṅgasūtra 9.1.14: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tasa-jīvā ya thāvarattāe</i>). "},"snp1.8:4.4":{"pli":"Majjhimā rassakā aṇukathūlā. ","eng":"medium, small, tiny or round, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:5.1":{"pli":"Diṭṭhā vā ye va adiṭṭhā, ","eng":"seen or unseen, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:5.2":{"pli":"Ye va dūre vasanti avidūre; ","eng":"living far or near, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:5.3":{"pli":"Bhūtā va sambhavesī va, ","eng":"those who have been born <j>and those about to be born—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"For “have become or will be” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>bhūtā va sambhavesī va</i>) I follow Norman and Bodhi in reading <i lang='pi' translate='no'>sambhavesī</i> as a future active participle. Compare such Sanskrit constructions as Rig Veda 1.66.8, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>yamo ha jāto yamo janitvaṁ</i> (“the twin that is born and the twin about to be born”) and Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 2.3.1.24, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>bhūtaṁ caiva bhaviṣyacca jātaṁ ca janiṣyamāṇaṁ</i> (“has become and will be, born and to be born”). "},"snp1.8:5.4":{"pli":"Sabbasattā bhavantu sukhitattā. ","eng":"may all beings be happy! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:6.1":{"pli":"Na paro paraṃ nikubbetha, ","eng":"Let none deceive another, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:6.2":{"pli":"Nātimaññetha katthaci na kañci; ","eng":"nor look down on anyone anywhere. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:6.3":{"pli":"Byārosanā paṭighasañña, ","eng":"Though provoked or aggrieved, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:6.4":{"pli":"Nāññamaññassa dukkhamiccheyya. ","eng":"let them not wish pain on each other. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:7.1":{"pli":"Mātā yathā niyaṃ puttam ","eng":"Even as a mother would protect with her life ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:7.2":{"pli":"Āyusā ekaputtamanurakkhe; ","eng":"her child, her only child, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:7.3":{"pli":"Evampi sabbabhūtesu, ","eng":"so too for all creatures ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:7.4":{"pli":"Mānasaṃ bhāvaye aparimāṇaṃ. ","eng":"unfold a boundless heart. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:8.1":{"pli":"Mettañca sabbalokasmi, ","eng":"With love for the whole world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:8.2":{"pli":"Mānasaṃ bhāvaye aparimāṇaṃ; ","eng":"unfold a boundless heart: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:8.3":{"pli":"Uddhaṃ adho ca tiriyañca, ","eng":"above, below, all round, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:8.4":{"pli":"Asambādhaṃ averamasapattaṃ. ","eng":"unconstricted, without enmity or foe. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:9.1":{"pli":"Tiṭṭhaṃ caraṃ nisinno va, ","eng":"When standing, walking, sitting, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:9.2":{"pli":"Sayāno yāvatāssa vitamiddho; ","eng":"or lying down while yet unweary, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:9.3":{"pli":"Etaṃ satiṃ adhiṭṭheyya, ","eng":"keep this ever in mind; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:9.4":{"pli":"Brahmametaṃ vihāramidhamāhu. ","eng":"for this, they say, is a divine meditation <j>in this life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.8:10.1":{"pli":"Diṭṭhiñca anupaggamma, ","eng":"Avoiding harmful views, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The final verse is set in a different meter, and given that the preceding verse already brings the poem to a satisfying conclusion, must be a later addition. Apparently the original poem was not Buddhist enough, and at some point more doctrinal material was felt to be needed. "},"snp1.8:10.2":{"pli":"Sīlavā dassanena sampanno; ","eng":"virtuous, accomplished in insight, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:10.3":{"pli":"Kāmesu vinaya gedhaṃ, ","eng":"with desire for sensual pleasures dispelled, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.8:10.4":{"pli":"Na hi jātuggabbhaseyya punaretī”ti. ","eng":"they never return to a womb again. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>","comm":"Note that <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jātu</i> here is not connected to <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jāti</i> “birth”. Rather, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>na hi jātu</i> is an idiom meaning “never”. Commentary: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ekaṁseneva</i>. "},"snp1.8:10.5":{"pli":"Mettasuttaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp1.9":{"snp1.9:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 1.9 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 1.9 ","html":"<article id='snp1.9'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp1.9:0.2":{"pli":"Hemavatasutta ","eng":"With Hemavata ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp1.9:1.1":{"pli":"“Ajja pannaraso uposatho, ","eng":"“Today is the fifteenth day sabbath,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:1.2":{"pli":"(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ","eng":"said Sātāgira, the native spirit of mount Sātā, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:1.3":{"pli":"Dibbā ratti upaṭṭhitā; ","eng":"“a holy night is at hand. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:1.4":{"pli":"Anomanāmaṃ satthāraṃ, ","eng":"Come now, let us see Gotama, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:1.5":{"pli":"Handa passāma gotamaṃ”. ","eng":"the Teacher of peerless name.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:2.1":{"pli":"“Kacci mano supaṇihito, ","eng":"“Isn’t his mind well-disposed,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:2.2":{"pli":"(iti hemavato yakkho) ","eng":"said Hemavata, the native spirit of the Himalayas, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:2.3":{"pli":"Sabbabhūtesu tādino; ","eng":"“impartial toward all creatures? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:2.4":{"pli":"Kacci iṭṭhe aniṭṭhe ca, ","eng":"And aren’t his thoughts under control ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:2.5":{"pli":"Saṅkappassa vasīkatā”. ","eng":"when it comes to likes and dislikes?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:3.1":{"pli":"“Mano cassa supaṇihito, ","eng":"“His mind is well-disposed,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:3.2":{"pli":"(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ","eng":"said Sātāgira, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:3.3":{"pli":"Sabbabhūtesu tādino; ","eng":"“impartial towards all creatures. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:3.4":{"pli":"Atho iṭṭhe aniṭṭhe ca, ","eng":"His thoughts are under control ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:3.5":{"pli":"Saṅkappassa vasīkatā”. ","eng":"when it comes to his likes and dislikes.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:4.1":{"pli":"“Kacci adinnaṃ nādiyati, ","eng":"“Doesn’t he not steal?” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:4.2":{"pli":"(iti hemavato yakkho) ","eng":"said Hemavata, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:4.3":{"pli":"Kacci pāṇesu saññato; ","eng":"“And doesn’t he harm not a creature? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:4.4":{"pli":"Kacci ārā pamādamhā, ","eng":"Isn’t he far from negligence? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:4.5":{"pli":"Kacci jhānaṃ na riñcati”. ","eng":"And doesn’t he not neglect absorption?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:5.1":{"pli":"“Na so adinnaṃ ādiyati, ","eng":"“He does not take what is not given,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:5.2":{"pli":"(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ","eng":"said Sātāgira, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:5.3":{"pli":"Atho pāṇesu saññato; ","eng":"“and he harms not a creature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:5.4":{"pli":"Atho ārā pamādamhā, ","eng":"He is far from negligence—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:5.5":{"pli":"Buddho jhānaṃ na riñcati”. ","eng":"the Buddha does not neglect absorption.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:6.1":{"pli":"“Kacci musā na bhaṇati, ","eng":"“Doesn’t he avoid lying?” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:6.2":{"pli":"(iti hemavato yakkho) ","eng":"said Hemavata, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:6.3":{"pli":"Kacci na khīṇabyappatho; ","eng":"“And doesn’t he not speak sharply? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:6.4":{"pli":"Kacci vebhūtiyaṃ nāha, ","eng":"Doesn’t he avoid divisive speech, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Norman has “untruth”, Bodhi “destructive”. Neither notices <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vebhūtiyaṁ</i> at  <a href='index.html?q=dn30#2.21.2'>DN 30:2.21.2</a> and <a href='index.html?q=dn28#11.2'>DN 28:11.2</a>, where “divisive” fits all cases. "},"snp1.9:6.5":{"pli":"Kacci samphaṃ na bhāsati”. ","eng":"as well as speaking nonsense?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:7.1":{"pli":"“Musā ca so na bhaṇati, ","eng":"“He does not lie,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:7.2":{"pli":"(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ","eng":"said Sātāgira, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:7.3":{"pli":"Atho na khīṇabyappatho; ","eng":"“nor does he speak sharply. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:7.4":{"pli":"Atho vebhūtiyaṃ nāha, ","eng":"He avoids divisive speech, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:7.5":{"pli":"Mantā atthañca bhāsati”. ","eng":"and thoughtfully speaks wise counsel.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"Following the sense at <a href='index.html?q=mn99#13.7'>MN 99:13.7</a>, where <i lang='pi' translate='no'>mantā</i> must mean “after thought”. "},"snp1.9:8.1":{"pli":"“Kacci na rajjati kāmesu, ","eng":"“Doesn’t he find sensual pleasures unattractive?” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:8.2":{"pli":"(iti hemavato yakkho) ","eng":"said Hemavata, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:8.3":{"pli":"Kacci cittaṃ anāvilaṃ; ","eng":"“And isn’t his mind unclouded? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:8.4":{"pli":"Kacci mohaṃ atikkanto, ","eng":"Hasn’t he escaped delusion? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:8.5":{"pli":"Kacci dhammesu cakkhumā”. ","eng":"Does his eye see clearly in all things?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:9.1":{"pli":"“Na so rajjati kāmesu, ","eng":"“He does not find sensual pleasures attractive,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:9.2":{"pli":"(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ","eng":"said Sātāgira, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:9.3":{"pli":"Atho cittaṃ anāvilaṃ; ","eng":"“and his mind is unclouded. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:9.4":{"pli":"Sabbamohaṃ atikkanto, ","eng":"He has escaped all delusion—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:9.5":{"pli":"Buddho dhammesu cakkhumā”. ","eng":"the Buddha, whose eye sees clearly in all things.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:10.1":{"pli":"“Kacci vijjāya sampanno, ","eng":"“Isn’t he accomplished in knowledge?” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:10.2":{"pli":"(iti hemavato yakkho) ","eng":"said Hemavata, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:10.3":{"pli":"Kacci saṃsuddhacāraṇo; ","eng":"“And doesn’t he live a pure life? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:10.4":{"pli":"Kaccissa āsavā khīṇā, ","eng":"Aren’t his defilements all ended? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:10.5":{"pli":"Kacci natthi punabbhavo”. ","eng":"Doesn’t he have no future lives?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:11.1":{"pli":"“Vijjāya ceva sampanno, ","eng":"“He is accomplished in knowledge,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:11.2":{"pli":"(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ","eng":"said Sātāgira, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:11.3":{"pli":"Atho saṃsuddhacāraṇo; ","eng":"“and he does live a pure life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:11.4":{"pli":"Sabbassa āsavā khīṇā, ","eng":"His defilements are all ended, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:11.5":{"pli":"Natthi tassa punabbhavo”. ","eng":"there’ll be no more future lives for him.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:12.1":{"pli":"“Sampannaṃ munino cittaṃ, ","eng":"“Accomplished is the sage’s mind ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:12.2":{"pli":"Kammunā byappathena ca; ","eng":"in action and in speech, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:12.3":{"pli":"Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, ","eng":"and he’s accomplished in knowledge and conduct ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:12.4":{"pli":"Dhammato naṃ pasaṃsati”. ","eng":"as per the teaching you praise.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"Read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pasaṁsasi</i> per PTS. "},"snp1.9:13.1":{"pli":"“Sampannaṃ munino cittaṃ, ","eng":"“Accomplished is the sage’s mind ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:13.2":{"pli":"Kammunā byappathena ca; ","eng":"in action and in speech, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:13.3":{"pli":"Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, ","eng":"and he’s accomplished in knowledge and conduct ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:13.4":{"pli":"Dhammato anumodasi. ","eng":"as per the teaching you rejoice in. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:14.1":{"pli":"Sampannaṃ munino cittaṃ, ","eng":"Accomplished is the sage’s mind ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:14.2":{"pli":"Kammunā byappathena ca; ","eng":"in action and in speech, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:14.3":{"pli":"Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, ","eng":"and he’s accomplished in knowledge and conduct: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:14.4":{"pli":"Handa passāma gotamaṃ”. ","eng":"come now, let us see Gotama.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:15.1":{"pli":"“Eṇijaṅghaṃ kisaṃ vīraṃ, ","eng":"“The hero so lean, with antelope calves, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:15.2":{"pli":"Appāhāraṃ alolupaṃ; ","eng":"not greedy, eating little, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:15.3":{"pli":"Muniṃ vanasmiṃ jhāyantaṃ, ","eng":"the sage meditating alone in the forest, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:15.4":{"pli":"Ehi passāma gotamaṃ. ","eng":"come now, let us see Gotama. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:16.1":{"pli":"Sīhaṃvekacaraṃ nāgaṃ, ","eng":"A giant, wandering alone like a lion, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:16.2":{"pli":"Kāmesu anapekkhinaṃ; ","eng":"unconcerned for sensual pleasures, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:16.3":{"pli":"Upasaṅkamma pucchāma, ","eng":"let’s approach him and ask about ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:16.4":{"pli":"Maccupāsappamocanaṃ. ","eng":"release from the snare of death.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:17.1":{"pli":"Akkhātāraṃ pavattāraṃ, ","eng":"“The communicator, the instructor, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:17.2":{"pli":"Sabbadhammāna pāraguṃ; ","eng":"who has gone beyond all things, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:17.3":{"pli":"Buddhaṃ verabhayātītaṃ, ","eng":"Awakened, beyond enmity and fear, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:17.4":{"pli":"Mayaṃ pucchāma gotamaṃ”. ","eng":"let us ask Gotama.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:18.1":{"pli":"“Kismiṃ loko samuppanno, ","eng":"“What has the world arisen in?” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:18.2":{"pli":"(iti hemavato yakkho) ","eng":"said Hemavata, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:18.3":{"pli":"Kismiṃ kubbati santhavaṃ; ","eng":"What does it get close to? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:18.4":{"pli":"Kissa loko upādāya, ","eng":"By grasping what ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:18.5":{"pli":"Kismiṃ loko vihaññati”. ","eng":"is the world troubled in what?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:19.1":{"pli":"“Chasu loko samuppanno, ","eng":"“The world’s arisen in six,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:19.2":{"pli":"(hemavatāti bhagavā) ","eng":"said the Buddha to Hemavata. ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:19.3":{"pli":"Chasu kubbati santhavaṃ; ","eng":"“It gets close to six. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:19.4":{"pli":"Channameva upādāya, ","eng":"Derived from the six, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:19.5":{"pli":"Chasu loko vihaññati”. ","eng":"the world’s troubled in six.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:20.1":{"pli":"“Katamaṃ taṃ upādānaṃ, ","eng":"“What is that grasping ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:20.2":{"pli":"Yattha loko vihaññati; ","eng":"by which the world is troubled? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:20.3":{"pli":"Niyyānaṃ pucchito brūhi, ","eng":"Tell us the exit when asked: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:20.4":{"pli":"Kathaṃ dukkhā pamuccati”. ","eng":"how is one released from all suffering?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:21.1":{"pli":"“Pañca kāmaguṇā loke, ","eng":"“The world has five kinds of sensual stimulation, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:21.2":{"pli":"Manochaṭṭhā paveditā; ","eng":"and the mind is said to be the sixth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:21.3":{"pli":"Ettha chandaṃ virājetvā, ","eng":"When you’ve discarded desire for these, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:21.4":{"pli":"Evaṃ dukkhā pamuccati. ","eng":"you’re released from all suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:22.1":{"pli":"Etaṃ lokassa niyyānaṃ, ","eng":"This is the exit from the world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:22.2":{"pli":"Akkhātaṃ vo yathātathaṃ; ","eng":"explained in accord with the truth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:22.3":{"pli":"Etaṃ vo ahamakkhāmi, ","eng":"The way I’ve explained it is how ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:22.4":{"pli":"Evaṃ dukkhā pamuccati”. ","eng":"you’re released from all suffering.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:23.1":{"pli":"“Ko sūdha tarati oghaṃ, ","eng":"“Who here crosses the flood, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:23.2":{"pli":"Kodha tarati aṇṇavaṃ; ","eng":"Who crosses the deluge? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:23.3":{"pli":"Appatiṭṭhe anālambe, ","eng":"Who, not standing and unsupported, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:23.4":{"pli":"Ko gambhīre na sīdati”. ","eng":"does not sink in the deep?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:24.1":{"pli":"“Sabbadā sīlasampanno, ","eng":"“Someone who is always endowed with ethics, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:24.2":{"pli":"Paññavā susamāhito; ","eng":"wise and serene, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:24.3":{"pli":"Ajjhattacintī satimā, ","eng":"inwardly reflective, mindful, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:24.4":{"pli":"Oghaṃ tarati duttaraṃ. ","eng":"crosses the flood so hard to cross. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:25.1":{"pli":"Virato kāmasaññāya, ","eng":"Someone who desists from sensual perception, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:25.2":{"pli":"Sabbasaṃyojanātigo; ","eng":"who has escaped all fetters, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:25.3":{"pli":"Nandībhavaparikkhīṇo, ","eng":"and has ended relish for rebirth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:25.4":{"pli":"So gambhīre na sīdati”. ","eng":"does not sink in the deep.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:26.1":{"pli":"“Gambhīrapaññaṃ nipuṇatthadassiṃ, ","eng":"“Behold him of wisdom deep <j>who sees the subtle meaning, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:26.2":{"pli":"Akiñcanaṃ kāmabhave asattaṃ; ","eng":"who has nothing, unattached to sensual life, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:26.3":{"pli":"Taṃ passatha sabbadhi vippamuttaṃ, ","eng":"everywhere free, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:26.4":{"pli":"Dibbe pathe kamamānaṃ mahesiṃ. ","eng":"the great seer treading the holy road. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:27.1":{"pli":"Anomanāmaṃ nipuṇatthadassiṃ, ","eng":"Behold him of peerless name <j>who sees the subtle meaning, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:27.2":{"pli":"Paññādadaṃ kāmālaye asattaṃ; ","eng":"giver of wisdom, <j>unattached to the realm of sensuality: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:27.3":{"pli":"Taṃ passatha sabbaviduṃ sumedhaṃ, ","eng":"see him, the all-knower, so very intelligent, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:27.4":{"pli":"Ariye pathe kamamānaṃ mahesiṃ. ","eng":"the great seer treading the noble road.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:28.1":{"pli":"Sudiṭṭhaṃ vata no ajja, ","eng":"“It was a fine sight for us today, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:28.2":{"pli":"Suppabhātaṃ suhuṭṭhitaṃ; ","eng":"a good dawn, a good rising, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:28.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ addasāma sambuddhaṃ, ","eng":"to see the Awakened One, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:28.4":{"pli":"Oghatiṇṇamanāsavaṃ. ","eng":"the undefiled one who has crossed the flood. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:29.1":{"pli":"Ime dasasatā yakkhā, ","eng":"These thousand native spirits ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:29.2":{"pli":"Iddhimanto yasassino; ","eng":"powerful and glorious, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:29.3":{"pli":"Sabbe taṃ saraṇaṃ yanti, ","eng":"all go to you for refuge, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:29.4":{"pli":"Tvaṃ no satthā anuttaro. ","eng":"you are our supreme Teacher. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp1.9:30.1":{"pli":"Te mayaṃ vicarissāma, ","eng":"We shall journey ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:30.2":{"pli":"Gāmā gāmaṃ nagā nagaṃ; ","eng":"village to village, peak to peak, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:30.3":{"pli":"Namassamānā sambuddhaṃ, ","eng":"paying homage to the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp1.9:30.4":{"pli":"Dhammassa ca sudhammatan”ti. ","eng":"and the clear rightness of the teaching!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp1.9:30.5":{"pli":"Hemavatasuttaṃ navamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}